    <item>
      <title>How To Study The Bible And Win $100</title>
      <link>http://www.bloggersbase.com/blogs/TGoodenough1/to-study-bible-win-100/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">http://www.bloggersbase.com/blogs/TGoodenough1/to-study-bible-win-100/</guid>
      <comments>http://www.bloggersbase.com/blogs/TGoodenough1/to-study-bible-win-100/</comments>
      <dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">
      </dc:creator>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Bible study site Biblefixit.com has released the information that it is now set to commence serving the online masses. Up til now the site has &amp;quot;lain fallow&amp;quot;, says the website's maker, Pastor Red Baxter, while he, of necessity, gave his attention to other things.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The site's thrust is to teach folks &lt;a href="http://biblefixit.com/how-to-study-the-bible.htm" rel="nofollow"&gt;how to study the bible&lt;/a&gt;. A premiere tool presented to scriptural learners is the site's &amp;quot;Bible Trivia Contest&amp;quot;, wherein all folks are allowed to participate, but small givers can get a $100 cash prize, as a compensation for displaying their grasp of &lt;a href="http://www.dailymotion.com/TGoodenough1#videoId=xkpfq4" rel="nofollow"&gt;bible facts&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The gifts, by contestants for the cash prize, are put to use to support the growth of a society named the &amp;quot;Tru U. Bible Brotherhood&amp;quot;. It is named the &amp;quot;Tru U.&amp;quot; for convenience. The reason for the Tru U. is to set up scripture teaching hours in people's houses, everywhere in the homeland.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Associates of the Tru U. Bible Brotherhood will become scripturally knowledgeable helpers, in centers called &amp;quot;Bible Fixit Hubs&amp;quot;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Pastor Red Baxter is known as a presbyter, or elder, of the order of Paul. In other words his authority is from direct revelation, rather than from the seminaries of the world order, which have, in the last few centuries, gone astray, says Pastor Baxter.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The trivia competitions take place in an online chat room. Questions are entered by the Biblefixit.com helpers. Whoever fastest keys the right answer gets the point. The contest ends, when one giver-player gets a 4-point margin beyond his leading competitor, who is also a donor. The front-runner is sent their $100 prize without delay, as soon as the game is over.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Biblefixit.com is an action-oriented site. There is a web page about destroying idols, and a page about ways to identify the descendants of Ammon and Moab in our own world, and how the holy scripture tells us to treat them. In addition to those pages, you will find also a web page on How To Study The Bible&amp;quot;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Obviously, if you desire to view the website for yourself, even participate for free in the trivia contest, the URL is biblefixit.com .&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/tgoodenough1s-personal-blog-on-bloggersbase/TGoodenough1s_personal_blog_on_BloggersBase-How_To_Study_The_Bible_And_Win_100.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <pubDate>Fri, 02 Sep 2011 21:27:48 GMT</pubDate>
